{"body": [{"indent": 0, "text": ["Carve"], "type": "title", "extent": [0, 10], "level": 0}, {"indent": 0, "type": "summary", "extent": [91, 166], "text": ["Slices, cuts or extracts points or cross-sections from a\nprimitive."]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [166, 365], "text": ["The Carve op works with any face or surface type, be that polygon,\nBezier, or NURBS. It can be used to slice a primitive, cut it into\nmultiple sections, or extract points or cross-sections from it."]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [365, 608], "text": ["Like the ", {"text": ["Project SOP"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/project", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/project"}, ", it also creates profile curves,\nbut they are extracted as iso-parametric (2D) profiles directly from a\nsurface, whereas the ", {"text": ["Project SOP"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/project", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/project"}, " extracts a 3D curve\nprojected onto a surface."]}, {"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [614, 709], "text": ["When using a Carve op on a trimmed surface, you can\u2019t fillet or join\n    the trim curves."]}], "indent": 0, "role": "item", "type": "note", "extent": [608, 614]}], "container": true, "role": "item_group", "type": "note_group"}, {"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 4, "blevel": 6, "type": "ord", "extent": [420, 468], "text": ["Select the faces or hulls to carve."]}, {"indent": 4, "blevel": 6, "type": "ord", "extent": [468, 555], "text": ["Click the ", {"text": "", "fullpath": "/shelf/SOP/carve", "scheme": "Icon", "type": "link", "value": "SOP/carve"}, {"text": ["Carve"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/carve", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/carve"}, " tool on the ", {"text": ["Model"], "type": "ui"}, " tab."]}, {"indent": 4, "blevel": 6, "type": "ord", "extent": [555, 653], "text": ["Specify what to slice, cut, or extract using the ", {"text": ["parameter editor"], "fullpath": "/ref/panes/parms", "scheme": null, "type": "link", "value": "/ref/panes/parms"}, ". "]}], "container": true, "type": "ord_group"}, {"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [653, 690], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/images/shelf/carve.png", "scheme": "Image", "type": "link", "value": "/images/shelf/carve.png"}]}], "indent": 0, "level": 2, "text": ["Using Carve"], "extent": [390, 420], "container": true, "type": "h", "id": "includeme"}, {"body": [{"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [788, 1021], "text": ["Given a closed surface, it can be converted to an identical open\n    surface at any location by using the Carve op, and cutting at a\n    single location (e.g. First U enabled, Second U disabled). The\n    same is true for faces."]}], "indent": 0, "type": "dt", "extent": [758, 788], "text": ["Opening a Closed Primitive"]}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [1048, 1348], "text": ["Select the Cut operation, First U = 0, Second U = 1, First V =\n    0, Second V = 1, with (at least) three divisions for U and V.\n    This will dice the surface into (at least) 3 x 3 components.\n    This can later be used with the ", {"text": ["Primitive\n    SOP"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/primitive", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/primitive"}, " to \"explode\" the surface."]}], "indent": 0, "type": "dt", "extent": [1021, 1048], "text": ["Dicing a Face or Surface"]}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [1378, 1619], "text": ["Select the Cut operation, First U = 0.33, Second U = 0.66, First\n    V = 0.33, Second V = 0.66, 2 divisions for U and V. Keep Inside\n    is off, Keep Outside is on. This will cut a rectangular region\n    from the center of the surface."]}], "indent": 0, "type": "dt", "extent": [1348, 1378], "text": ["Cutting a Hole in a Surface"]}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [1662, 1894], "text": ["Select the Extract option, First U = x, Last U disabled, First V\n    = y, Last V disabled, Extract Point is on, Keep Primitives is\n    optional. This will create a point over any position on the\n    surface (0<=x<=1, 0<=y<=1)."]}], "indent": 0, "type": "dt", "extent": [1619, 1662], "text": ["Animating a Point Over a Face or Surface"]}], "container": true, "type": "dt_group"}], "indent": 0, "level": 2, "text": ["Tips"], "extent": [747, 758], "container": true, "type": "h", "id": null}, {"body": [{"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [1917, 1968], "text": ["Specifies a subset of primitives to carve."]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["Group"], "role": "item", "extent": [1906, 1917], "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [2011, 2057], "text": ["Starting location in the U direction."]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["First U"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"channels": "/domainu1"}, "extent": [1968, 1981], "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [2101, 2144], "text": ["Ending location for the operation."]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["Second U"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"channels": "/domainu2"}, "extent": [2057, 2071], "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [2188, 2237], "text": ["Number of cuts/extracts to be performed."]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["U Divisions"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"channels": "/divsu"}, "extent": [2144, 2161], "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [2276, 2381], "text": ["Cut only at ends or along all internal breakpoints. Only At\n        Breakpoints must be toggled."]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["Cut At All Internal U Breakpoints"], "role": "item", "extent": [2237, 2276], "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [2424, 2470], "text": ["Starting location in the V direction."]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["First V"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"channels": "/domainv1"}, "extent": [2381, 2394], "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [2514, 2557], "text": ["Ending location for the operation."]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["Second V"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"channels": "/domainv2"}, "extent": [2470, 2484], "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [2601, 2650], "text": ["Number of cuts/extracts to be performed."]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["V Divisions"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"channels": "/divsv"}, "extent": [2557, 2574], "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [2689, 2794], "text": ["Cut only at ends or along all internal breakpoints. Only At\n        Breakpoints must be toggled."]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["Cut At All Internal V Breakpoints"], "role": "item", "extent": [2650, 2689], "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [2803, 2858], "text": ["Splits primitive at locations specified above."]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["Cut"], "role": "item", "extent": [2794, 2803], "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [2875, 2932], "text": ["Keeps the primitives between First and Second U."]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["Keep Inside"], "role": "item", "extent": [2858, 2875], "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [2950, 3007], "text": ["Keeps the primitives outside First and Second U."]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["Keep Outside"], "role": "item", "extent": [2932, 2950], "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [3020, 3326], "text": ["Extracts points, cross-sections, or curves-on-surface along each\n        location specified above. Only points can be extracted from a\n        face and the V parameter has no effect. Extraction of\n        cross-sections and curves-on surface is possible only if the\n        primitive is a surface."]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["Extract"], "role": "item", "extent": [3007, 3020], "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [3345, 3406], "text": ["Will keep the original primitive from being removed."]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["Keep Original"], "role": "item", "extent": [3326, 3345], "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [3431, 3587], "text": ["Perform the operation only at breakpoints for NURBS and Bezier\n        surfaces or faces and at vertices for polygonal faces and\n        surfaces."]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["Only At Breakpoints"], "role": "item", "extent": [3406, 3431], "type": "parameters_item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group", "type": "parameters_item_group"}], "indent": 0, "level": 1, "text": "Parameters", "role": "section", "extent": [1894, 1906], "container": true, "type": "parameters_section", "id": "parameters"}, {"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 4, "blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "extent": [3596, 3618], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/trim", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/trim"}]}, {"indent": 4, "blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "extent": [3618, 3644], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/surfsect", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/surfsect"}]}, {"indent": 4, "blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "extent": [3644, 3671], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/curvesect", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/curvesect"}]}, {"indent": 4, "blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "extent": [3671, 3695], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/cookie", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/cookie"}]}, {"indent": 4, "blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "extent": [3695, 3718], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/clip", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/clip"}]}], "container": true, "type": "bullet_group"}], "indent": 0, "level": 1, "text": "Related", "role": "section", "extent": [3587, 3596], "container": true, "type": "related_section", "id": "related"}], "title": ["Carve"], "summary": ["Slices, cuts or extracts points or cross-sections from a\nprimitive."], "attrs": {"version": null, "tags": "tech, model", "namespace": null, "internal": "carve", "context": "sop", "type": "node", "icon": "SOP/carve"}, "included": ["/shelf/carve"], "type": "root"}